GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE RESOLUTION 761
Sponsors: Senator Rabon (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: State and Local Government
April 29, 2025
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION RELATING TO THE APPOINTMENT, NOMINATION, AND
2 CONFIRMATION OF TEENA PICCIONE AS THE STATE CHIEF INFORMATION
3 OFFICER AND SECRETARY OF THE DEPARTMENT OF INFORMATION
4 TECHNOLOGY.
5 Whereas, pursuant to G.S. 143B-9(a), the Governor shall notify the President of the
6 Senate of the name of each person to be nominated as head of a principal State department; and
7 Whereas, each nomination is subject to senatorial advice and consent in conformance
8 with Section 5(8) of Article III of the North Carolina Constitution; and
9 Whereas, the Governor has appointed Teena Piccione to serve as the State Chief
10 Information Officer and Secretary of the Department of Information Technology pending further
11 action by the Senate; Now, therefore,
12 Be it resolved by the Senate:
13 SECTION 1. That the Senate shall hereby consider whether to confirm Teena
14 Piccione as the State Chief Information Officer and Secretary of the Department of Information
15 Technology.
16 SECTION 2. This resolution is effective upon adoption.
*S761-v-1*

